 How to use this repository
============================

1. cd $HOME
2. git clone <repository> .vim
3. ln -s .vim/vimrc .vimrc
4. cd .vim
5. git submodule init
6. git submodule update

This Vim configuration uses Pathogen (http://github.com/tpope/vim-pathogen),
the plugins are placed in `.vim/bundle/'. Some of the plugins are hosted in
GitHub so I use Git submodules to track those plugins in `.vim/bundle/' as
separate repositories.


 Working with Git submodules
-----------------------------

- To add a new submodule (and download the latest revision from GIT-URL):
	git submodule add GIT-URL bundle/<plugin>

- When this Vim repository is cloned, the submodules directories are
  empty. So to pull submodules in their places, run from top level
  directory:
	git submodule init
	git submodule update

- When the remote repository of one of the submodules is updated with new
  commits, this will not be automatically pulled to our plugins
  directories. So go to some plugin directory controlled as a submodule
  and run there:
	git pull
	(Now go to the top level directory and commit changes)
